rComments: Favourite UofT Prof BY FAR! Class is HARD, but REWARDING. Coursework is intense, but clear and fair (a rarity in this department). No lecture slides (however, she posts outlines)  you have to take notes  you have to come to class. Got an A-, but Ive never felt more accomplished. Warning: Prof likes in-class essay midterms and 9am finals.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Bryant changed my perspectives on Bioethics. I used to laugh at some of the case studies she would give us. I remember one case where a patient life saving refused life saving treatment from his Dr. I thought this had to be the dumbest patient in the world until this Prof helped me understand the patient's POV. Recommended for med school hopefuls

If you have anything negative to say about her, you're probably an idiot. Great prof. Easy marker. If you take time to talk to her, you'll be able to tell she loves what she does. U of T should hold on to her.

She is very involved in the course, but her lecture is not very clear. She says 'um' a lot and looks down most of the time. Her essays are difficult. A tip to get good mark on the essay is to have good structure to it. She gave us exam questions one week before the exam which is very helpful. Overall, this course is not hard if you read the require

looks down a lot. Uses lots of "ums" when speaking. Her essays were challenging, but if you know how to structure it you can get a good mark. She gave us the essay questions ahead of the exam!! Gave us a good broad spectrum of what environmental philosophy entails.
